<paragraph id="122836C01F1C6D3CAAD7FA88FE95B91C" blockId="7.[189,303,1375,1401]" box="[189,303,1375,1401]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<heading id="496081AC1F1C6D3CAAD7FA88FE95B91C" bold="true" box="[189,303,1375,1401]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" reason="3">
<emphasis id="20E3EAD21F1C6D3CAAD7FA88FE95B91C" bold="true" box="[189,303,1375,1401]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="122836C01F1C6D3CAAD7FA59FC82BA1A" blockId="7.[189,1399,1422,1663]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
The 
<typeStatus id="CD2C88621F1C6D3CAA98FA59FE9FB9CD" box="[242,293,1422,1448]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName id="D5974D431F1C6D3CABE2FA59FD33B9CD" authority="Kanesharatnam &amp; Benjamin, 2018" authorityName="Kanesharatnam &amp; Benjamin" authorityYear="2018" box="[392,649,1422,1448]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Bavirecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavopuncta" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="20E3EAD21F1C6D3CABE2FA59FD33B9CD" box="[392,649,1422,1448]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Bavirecta flavopuncta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="3BD057A91F1C6D3CA8FBFA59FCFBB9CD" box="[657,833,1422,1448]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D5974D431F1C6D3CA910FA59FC62B9CD" authorityName="Kanesharatnam &amp; Benjamin" authorityYear="2018" box="[890,984,1422,1448]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Bavia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exilis" status="gen. et comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="20E3EAD21F1C6D3CA910FA59FC62B9CD" box="[890,984,1422,1448]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. exilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="3BD057A91F1C6D3CA98AFA59FB0DB9CD" box="[992,1207,1422,1448]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" rank="species">gen. et comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
are very similar to each other in somatic as well as genital morphology. Both species differ considerably in genital structures from the 
<typeStatus id="CD2C88621F1C6D3CABC2FA01FE61B995" box="[424,475,1494,1520]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName id="D5974D431F1C6D3CA809FA01FD1DB98A" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1877" box="[611,679,1494,1519]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Bavia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="20E3EAD21F1C6D3CA809FA01FD1DB98A" box="[611,679,1494,1519]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Bavia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D5974D431F1C6D3CA8D2FA01FC87B98A" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1877" box="[696,829,1494,1519]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Bavia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aericeps">
<emphasis id="20E3EAD21F1C6D3CA8D2FA01FC87B98A" box="[696,829,1494,1519]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. aericeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see discussion below). 
<taxonomicName id="D5974D431F1C6D3CAE0FFA01FAA7B98A" authorityName="Kanesharatnam &amp; Benjamin" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Cao, Li &amp; Zabka" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[1125,1309,1493,1519]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Bavirecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exilis" status="gen. et comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="20E3EAD21F1C6D3CAE0FFA01FAA7B98A" box="[1125,1309,1493,1519]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Bavirecta exilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="3BD057A91F1C6D3CAF4CFA01FEF8BA71" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" rank="species">gen. et comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
shares the presence of a short, straight embolus and the broad PLT with 
<taxonomicName id="D5974D431F1C6D3CAED7FA2DFAD5BA76" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1877" box="[1213,1391,1530,1555]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Bavia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aericeps">
<emphasis id="20E3EAD21F1C6D3CAED7FA2DFAD5BA76" box="[1213,1391,1530,1555]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Bavia aericeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D5974D431F1C6D3CAAD7F9C9FEE3BA52" baseAuthorityName="C. L. Koch" baseAuthorityYear="1846" box="[189,345,1566,1591]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Bavia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capistrata">
<emphasis id="20E3EAD21F1C6D3CAAD7F9C9FEE3BA52" box="[189,345,1566,1591]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. capistrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D5974D431F1C6D3CABF0F9C9FD87BA52" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Karsch" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[410,573,1565,1591]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Bavia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis id="20E3EAD21F1C6D3CABF0F9C9FD87BA52" box="[410,573,1565,1591]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, it differs from them by the relatively long RTA and the well-developed retrolateral membranous margin of the embolus. 
<taxonomicName id="D5974D431F1C6D3CA9AAF995FBCDBA3E" authorityName="Kanesharatnam &amp; Benjamin" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Cao, Li &amp; Zabka" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[960,1143,1601,1627]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Bavirecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exilis" status="gen. et comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="20E3EAD21F1C6D3CA9AAF995FBCDBA3E" box="[960,1143,1601,1627]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Bavirecta exilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="3BD057A91F1C6D3CAEEAF996FAE1BA3E" box="[1152,1371,1601,1627]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" rank="species">gen. et comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is described in detail and diagnosed in 
<bibRefCitation id="76064B311F1C6D3CA800F9B2FC8EBA1A" author="Cao X. W. &amp; Li S. Q. &amp; Zabka M." box="[618,820,1636,1663]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="43 - 104" refId="ref8015" refString="Cao X. W., Li S. Q. &amp; Zabka M. 2016. The jumping spiders from Xishuangbanna, Yunnan, China (Araneae, Salticidae). ZooKeys 630: 43 - 104. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 630.8466" type="journal article" year="2016">
Cao 
<emphasis id="20E3EAD21F1C6D3CA8CAF9B2FD6EBA1A" box="[672,724,1637,1663]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">et al</emphasis>
. (2016)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
